ginal {{ill|Miyama Shrine|ja|御山神社}} to the current Sanki-dō.

=== Origin ===
It is believed that the revered monk {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海}} (also known as Kōbō Daishi) enshrined Sanki Daigongen in 806 CE (Daido 1) when he founded Mount Misen as a sacred site.

=== Mantra ===
The mantra associated with Sanki Daigongen is:
* '''On Aratan Nō Un Sowaka''' (オン・アラタンノウ・ウン・ソワカ).

Additionally, there are {{ill|wasan|ja|和讃}} (Buddhist hymns) praising the virtues of Sanki Daigongen.

